    "Concurrently, to ensure model efficiency and ease of deployment, we employ lightweight S3D [12] and Sign Language Graph Convolution Network [16] as the backbone.",
    "Sign language applicationsAs Artificial Intelligence (AI) advances, numerous models and applications have emerged, each designed to enhance communication and offer assistance to humans [19][20][21][22][23][24].",
    "Meanwhile, there are also many AI programs specifically focused on sign language [17,[25][26][27][28].",
    "However, current efforts in sign language applications primarily exhibit two major shortcomings.",
    "First, they only support translating spoken language input into sign language and do not facilitate the translation of sign language input back into spoken language."
